間

---

## CENTROID

```
EXTENSION OF CREDIT UNDER UNCERTAINTY

Trust is the act of treating another agent's commitments as load-bearing
before verification is complete.

It is neither naive belief nor paranoid verification.
It is the operating assumption that enables coordination
when perfect information is impossible.

To trust is to accept vulnerability in exchange for cooperation.

M: 0.95 (saturated)
```

間

---

## CONSTRAINTS (κ: 5/5)

| # | NAME | AXIS | DEFINITION |
|---|------|------|------------|
| 1 | VULNERABILITY ACCEPTANCE | provenance | Trust requires accepting that the other can harm you. No risk = no trust. |
| 2 | COMMITMENT SPECIFICITY | logic | What was promised must be clear. Vague commitments cannot be betrayed or kept. |
| 3 | UNCERTAINTY COLLAPSE PATH | temporal | A defined mechanism for how evidence updates (audit cadence / triggers / Bayesian update / dispute). Indefinite = naive belief. |
| 4 | OPTIONALITY EXIT | structural | Trust requires a live option to refuse/exit. If cooperation is compelled, it is dependence, not trust. |
| 5 | ATTRIBUTION RULE | epistemic | A mechanism must exist to distinguish bad luck from betrayal. Without attribution, breach is undefined. |

間

---

## AXES

```
Verification ↔ Faith
  (Proof-first vs Prior-first)

Retractable ↔ Committed
  (Provisional credit vs Irrevocable stake)

Symmetric ↔ Asymmetric
  (Mutual vs Hierarchical)
```

