## VOID (9)

```
∅ naive_belief            -.90 | accepting claims without verification; violates C3
∅ coercive_trust          -.85 | trust extracted via power; violates C4 (no exit)
∅ paranoid_verification   -.85 | requiring proof of everything; violates centroid
∅ blind_authority         -.80 | trusting role without audit; violates C5
∅ reputation_portability  -.78 | trust moves without lineage check
∅ vague_commitments       -.75 | unverifiable promises; violates C2
∅ performative_transparency -.72 | flooding data to hide; violates C5
∅ moral_licensing         -.70 | "I trusted before, so you owe me now"
∅ trust_hostage           -.68 | contingent on unverifiable claims; violates C2+C4
```

